OL,3,GOPINIONCGreen paper recognises the
OL,4,Cimportance of the BBC
OL,5,
OL,6,FIt should be no surprise that a green
OL,7,Fpaper from a Labour government is not
OL,8,Fpandering to philosophical or
OL,9,Fideological critics on the right `
OL,10,Fthose who would want the BBC
OL,11,Fprivatised, abolished or significantly
OL,12,Fsmaller in scale.
OL,14,FOne area for debate is funding. Are
OL,15,Fthere realistic alternatives to the
OL,16,Flicence fee?
OL,18,FNothing is off the table at this stage
OL,19,Fother than direct funding from general
OL,20,Ftaxation.
