OL,3,GOPINIONCGreen paper recognises the
OL,4,Cimportance of the BBC
OL,5,
OL,6,FInstead of a flat fee, is there a way
OL,7,Fto create some link with the ability of
OL,8,Fsomeone to pay? What about people who
OL,9,Fdon't have a TV (or access to iPlayer)
OL,10,Fbut who listen to BBC Radio or use the
OL,11,Frest of the website?
OL,13,FThe idea of a household charge `
OL,14,Flinked, perhaps, to council tax bands `
OL,15,Fhas attractions. But there needs to be
OL,16,Fa proper debate on pros and cons.
OL,18,FI actually would not be completely
OL,19,Fsurprised if the licence fee survives
OL,20,Fagain, perhaps with minor modifications
OL,21,For discounts for the poorest.
