OL,3,GOPINIONCGreen paper recognises the
OL,4,Cimportance of the BBC
OL,5,
OL,6,FIn a way, it has only become a flat
OL,7,Frate fee over the past 30 years.
OL,9,FUntil the early 60s, those on the
OL,10,Flowest incomes may well not have had a
OL,11,FTV ` just a radio.
OL,13,FColour TVs were aspirational items for
OL,14,Fmuch of the 70s. Those on low incomes
OL,15,For with other priorities would have
OL,16,Fbeen likely to watch in black and
OL,17,Fwhite.
